                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1002">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.75 National Telephone Co./360: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bucknell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-09T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 9, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 9—8:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>114. My telegram No. 113, May 8, 9 p.m. I am informed by members of the Telephone
                    Company that a representative of the Minister <pb facs="0894" n="885"
                        xml:id="pg_885"/> of Finance is now proceeding to Paris to resume
                    discussions with Morgans in an effort to obtain a loan<note n="89"
                        xml:id="d1002fn89">The Department in telegram No. 60, May 13, 7 p.m.,
                        informed the Embassy in Spain as follows: “There is every reason to believe
                        that Morgans will not consider under present circumstances the transaction
                        discussed.”</note> from that bank for the Spanish Government. Under the
                    circumstances the Department may consider it advisable to notify the Embassy in
                    Paris of the inconclusive results so far obtained with regard to the final
                    settlement of the Telephone Company case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucknell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
